Katsina State Government has lifted ban on Sunday Church service, telling Christian faithful and churches in particular to observe one hour worship session. The Secretary to the State government (SSG), Alhaji Mustapha Muhammad Inuwa, made the announcement in a statement made available to Leadership on yesterday, said “government had met with Christian clerics and reviewed the orders that affect weekly religious services in the state. “Further to the government’s continuous review of the measures taken to curb the spread of Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic in the state. “The governor has directed lifting of the suspension of Sunday Church Services with immediate effect. “The services, however, are to be conducted under stipulated health and security guidelines. “Church Services should not be prolonged in order to discharge the followers within a short period, which after due consultations, agreed to be conducted within one hour.” He therefore, urged the people to maintain social distancing and adhere strictly to all rules and regulations provided by health experts in fighting the rampaging disease.